Options:

-h, --help 
  
   Displays me :).
   
-H, --hostname <HOSTNAME> 
  
   Default is `127.0.0.1`. Sets the ElasticSearch hostname. Note: The complete ElasticSearch host can also be defined over the env argument `ES_URL`.
   
-p, --port <PORT> 
  
   Default is `9200`. Sets the ElasticSearch port. Note: The complete ElasticSearch host can also be defined over the env argument `ES_URL`.
   
-l, --list <FILTER> 
  
   Default is `*`. Lists all aliases/indices matching the given filter.
   
-c, --create <NAME> 
  
   Creates an index with the given name following by a timestamp.
   
-a, --activate <NAME-TIMESTAMP> 
  
   Deletes (if exitsts) the alias `NAME` and assigns the alias `NAME` to the given index.
   
-s, --swap <NAME-TIMESTAMP> 
  
   Deletes (if exitsts) the alias `NAME-TIMESTAMP-write` and assigns the alias `NAME` to the given index.
   
-r, --remove <NAME> 
  
   Deletes expired indices matching the given name.
   
-o, --older <N> 
  
   Default is 1 day. Sets the limit for valid indices in days. Set to 'none' to remove all unreferenced indices.
   
-y, --yes 
  
   Assume `Yes` to all questions.
   

